<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="272" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[132,777,1286,1508]" box="[132,232,1286,1312]" pageId="15" pageNumber="272">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[132,777,1286,1508]" pageId="15" pageNumber="272">
Koehler’s original description mentions 
<specimenCount box="[593,774,1318,1344]" pageId="15" pageNumber="272" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
(Scotia 
<collectingRegion box="[217,258,1352,1378]" country="Cayman Islands" name="West Bay" pageId="15" pageNumber="272">Bay</collectingRegion>
, South Orcads, 
<quantity box="[433,495,1351,1378]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="15" pageNumber="272" unit="m" value="18.0">18 m</quantity>
). Yet 
<specimenCount box="[555,710,1351,1377]" pageId="15" pageNumber="272" type="generic">five specimens</specimenCount>
occur in the 
<collectingRegion box="[205,297,1384,1410]" country="Ireland" name="Monaghan" pageId="15" pageNumber="272">MNHN</collectingRegion>
with a single label indicating they are from the 
<typeStatus box="[173,219,1417,1443]" pageId="15" pageNumber="272">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[132,777,1286,1508]" pageId="15" pageNumber="272">
Various 
<typeStatus box="[243,334,1450,1476]" pageId="15" pageNumber="272">syntypes</typeStatus>
(15) are housed in the RSM (Ref. 1921. 143.1232) (Smalon 
<emphasis box="[351,402,1482,1508]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="272">et al.</emphasis>
1976).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
